課程概述 Course Description
       以流體力學角度深入探討各式流體力學相關主題，從建立數學模型到實際流場驗證以訓練學生獨立流場分析與應用的能力。 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    The purpose of this course is to expose engineering students to the principles and implementation of diversely experimental and numerical techniques with a systematic look at engineering practice of fluid mechanics. The course begins with a review of basic formulations and constitutive models of fluid mechanics. Key topics include nature and real-world engineering examples such as fish suction feeding, fish schooling, cannula design, abdominal aortic aneurysm flow, anti-locking brake system, and wind turbine. Other topics of interest can be discussed as well if time permits. Throughout the course, both analytical and numerical results are presented in conjunction with selected readings from journal articles and the relevance of these results to the associated engineering fields is highlighted. Students will need to apply the material learned from the class into a final project with topics of their choice. Basic skills in computer programming are desired.     

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Introduction to Fluid Mechanics2Non-Newtonian Flow Model3Numerical modeling4Experimental flow assessment5Fish Suction Feeding6Fish Schooling7Cilia8Cannula Design9Aortic Blood Flow10Dean Flow11Midterm12Anti-locking Brake System and Final Project-113Wind Turbine and Final Project-214Fluid Film Lubrication15Final Project Workshop16Final Project Workshop17Guest Lecture18Project Presentations (Final report due) 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


